    {
      "text": "Ribbit King is a 2003 sports video game developed by Infinity and Jamsworks and published by Bandai for the GameCube and PlayStation 2. The game is based on the fictional sport of Frolf (ケロフ), which is a golf-like game that is played with frogs. The frogs sit on catapults, which the player whacks with a hammer to send the frog flying into the air. It is the successor to Kero Kero King, released only in Japan in 2000 for the PlayStation.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
